twap_ind_sids_aqbuffcapacity-bm.def: Volume of groundwater stored in the aquifer [m3] divided by groundwater recharge [m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_aqbuffcapacity-bm.name: S1.4 Buffering capacity

twap_ind_sids_aqvulnerabilityclimchange-.def: Expected groundwater budget regime change in response to changes in climatic conditions. Indicator takes into account the degree of confinement, aquifer lithology, recharge and depth to groundwater table (see TWAP Groundwater methodology report for details).
twap_ind_sids_aqvulnerabilityclimchange-.name: S1.5 Vulnerability to climate change

twap_ind_sids_aqvulnerabilitypollution-b.def: Percentage of surface area where the aquifer is considered moderately to highly vulnerable to pollution. Indicator takes into account the degree of confinement, aquifer lithology and depth to groundwater table (see TWAP Groundwater methodology report for details).
twap_ind_sids_aqvulnerabilitypollution-b.name: S1.6 Vulnerability to pollution

twap_ind_sids_controlgwabstraction-bm.def: Current practices on the implementation of measures to control groundwater abstraction.
twap_ind_sids_controlgwabstraction-bm.name: S6.1 Control groundwater abstraction

twap_ind_sids_ecosystdepgw-bm.def: Percentage of surface area of the aquifer where the phreatic water level is less than 5 m below the surface, or percentage of surface area of the aquifer covered by groundwater dependent ecosystems.
twap_ind_sids_ecosystdepgw-bm.name: S2.5 Ecosystem dependency on groundwater

twap_ind_sids_gwdepletion2-bm.def: Observed rate of long-term progressive decrease of groundwater storage (accompanied by steadily declining groundwater levels), expressed as an equivalent depth of water averaged over the island area. Preferred period: 2000-2010.
twap_ind_sids_gwdepletion2-bm.name: S3.1 Groundwater depletion

twap_ind_sids_gwdevelopmentstress-bm.def: Total annual groundwater abstraction [m3/yr] divided by groundwater recharge [m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_gwdevelopmentstress-bm.name: S4.2 Groundwater development stress

twap_ind_sids_gwpollution-bm.def: Observed areal extent of polluted zones as a percentage of total aquifer area.
twap_ind_sids_gwpollution-bm.name: S3.2 Groundwater pollution

twap_ind_sids_gwqualityprotection-bm.def: Current practices on the implementation of groundwater quality protection.
twap_ind_sids_gwqualityprotection-bm.name: S6.2 Groundwater quality protection

twap_ind_sids_humandepgw-bm.def: Volume of groundwater used [m3/yr] expressed as a percentage of total volume of water used [m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_humandepgw-bm.name: S2.1 Human dependency on groundwater

twap_ind_sids_humandepgwagricult-bm.def: Volume of groundwater for agricultural use [m3/yr] expressed as a percentage of total agricultural water use [m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_humandepgwagricult-bm.name: S2.3 Human dependency on groundwater for agricultural use [%]

twap_ind_sids_humandepgwdomestic-bm.def: Volume of groundwater for domestic use [m3/yr] expressed as a percentage of total domestic water use [m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_humandepgwdomestic-bm.name: S2.2 Human dependency on groundwater for domestic use

twap_ind_sids_humandepgwindustry-bm.def: Volume of groundwater for industrial use [m3/yr] expressed as a percentage of total industrial water use m3/yr].
twap_ind_sids_humandepgwindustry-bm.name: S2.4 Human dependency on groundwater for industrial use

twap_ind_sids_mannualgwrechargedepth-bm.def: Long-term average groundwater recharge (including man-made components like return-flows, induced recharge and artificial recharge) [m3/yr], divided by the surface area of the island [m2]. Unit: [mm/yr] or [litre/m2/yr].
twap_ind_sids_mannualgwrechargedepth-bm.name: S1.1 Groundwater recharge

twap_ind_sids_mannualrenewablegwpercap-b.def: Groundwater recharge (including man-made components like return-flows, induced recharge and artificial recharge) [m3/yr], divided by the number of inhabitants on top of the aquifer [capita].
twap_ind_sids_mannualrenewablegwpercap-b.name: S1.2 Renewable groundwater resources per capita

twap_ind_sids_natbackgwquality-bm.def: Percentage of surface area of the aquifer where the natural groundwater quality satisfies local drinking water standards (i.e. percentage of aquifer area which is not affected by natural salinity, arsenic, fluoride, etc.).
twap_ind_sids_natbackgwquality-bm.name: S1.3 Natural groundwater quality

twap_ind_sids_popdensity-bm.def: Number of inhabitants of the island [capita] divided by surface area of the island [km2].
twap_ind_sids_popdensity-bm.name: S4.1 Population density

twap_ind_sids_prevelancesprings-bm.def: Average annual groundwater discharge by springs [m3/yr] divided by Groundwater recharge [m3/yr]. (Springs are very sensitive to changes in groundwater budget, either from change in recharge or change in abstraction regime. Therefore spring discharge is a meaningful indicator of change.).
twap_ind_sids_prevelancesprings-bm.name: S2.6 Prevalence of springs

twap_ind_sids_saltwaterintrusion-bm.def: Observed zones of saltwater intrusion as a percentage of total island area (due to salinity exceeding drinking water quality standards).
twap_ind_sids_saltwaterintrusion-bm.name: S3.3 Saltwater intrusion

twap_ind_sids_transbinstframework-bm.def: Existence, mandate and capabilities of institutions or institutional arrangements for managing SIDS groundwater.
twap_ind_sids_transbinstframework-bm.name: S5.2 SIDS institutional framework

twap_ind_sids_transblegalframework-bm.def: Existence, status and comprehensiveness of groundwater legislation.
twap_ind_sids_transblegalframework-bm.name: S5.1 SIDS legal framework
